-# ![Logo](chrome/app/theme/chromium/product_logo_64.png) Chromium
+# Aster Browser
 
-Chromium is an open-source browser project that aims to build a safer, faster,
-and more stable way for all users to experience the web.
+[![Contributors][contributors-shield]][contributors-url]
+[![Forks][forks-shield]][forks-url]
+[![Stars][stars-shield]][stars-url]
+[![Issues][issues-shield]][issues-url]
+[![License][license-shield]][license-url]
 
-The project's web site is https://www.chromium.org.
+Aster Browser is a Chromium-based browser project maintained by Aster Team.
+The project keeps Chromium's web platform foundation while replacing the
+browser-facing identity with Aster.
 
-To check out the source code locally, don't use `git clone`! Instead,
-follow [the instructions on how to get the code](docs/get_the_code.md).
+## Repository
 
-Documentation in the source is rooted in [docs/README.md](docs/README.md).
+- Project: [jiho-m0521/Aster-Browser](https://github.com/jiho-m0521/Aster-Browser)
+- Maintainer: [Aster Team](https://github.com/jiho-m0521/Aster-Browser)
+- Upstream base: [Chromium](https://www.chromium.org/)
 
-Learn how to [Get Around the Chromium Source Code Directory
-Structure](https://www.chromium.org/developers/how-tos/getting-around-the-chrome-source-code).
+## What Changed
 
-For historical reasons, there are some small top level directories. Now the
-guidance is that new top level directories are for product (e.g. Chrome,
-Android WebView, Ash). Even if these products have multiple executables, the
-code should be in subdirectories of the product.
+- Product name and short name are branded as `Aster`.
+- Browser UI strings such as About, update status, default browser prompts, and
+  related settings copy use Aster naming.
+- Product metadata uses `Aster Team`.
+- The About copyright string is `Copyright 2026 Aster Team. All rights reserved.`
 
-If you found a bug, please file it at https://crbug.com/new.
+## Getting Started
+
+This repository follows the Chromium checkout and build flow. For a fresh
+checkout, use Chromium's depot_tools workflow rather than a plain `git clone`.
+
+```powershell
+gclient sync
+```
+
+Generate build files:
+
+```powershell
+$env:DEPOT_TOOLS_WIN_TOOLCHAIN = "0"
+$env:GYP_MSVS_OVERRIDE_PATH = "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\18\Insiders"
+gn gen out\Default
+```
+
+Build Aster:
+
+```powershell
+autoninja -C out\Default chrome
+```
+
+Run the browser:
+
+```powershell
+out\Default\chrome.exe --user-data-dir=C:\chromium\test-profile
+```
+
+## Verification
+
+After building, open `chrome://version`. The application label should show
+`Aster`.
+
+The current Windows build output is expected under:
+
+```text
+C:\chromium\src\out\Default\chrome.exe
+```
+
+## Contributing
+
+Use feature branches and send changes to:
+
+```text
+https://github.com/jiho-m0521/Aster-Browser
+```
+
+Suggested local remote setup:
+
+```powershell
+git remote add upstream https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src.git
+git remote set-url origin https://github.com/jiho-m0521/Aster-Browser.git
+```
+
+## License
+
+Aster Browser is based on Chromium and retains Chromium's open-source license
+notices. See [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.
